%pyspark
inPatientAll = spark.read.csv("hdfs://dumbo/user/mm9817/Medicare/Inpatient_combined/InpatientAll.csv",header=True)
outPatientAll = spark.read.csv("hdfs://dumbo/user/mm9817/Medicare/Outpatient_combined/Outpatient_All.csv",header=True)

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import SQLContext
sqlContext = SQLContext(spark)

%pyspark
inPatientAll.registerTempTable('inPatientAll')
outPatientAll.registerTempTable('outPatientAll')
test = sqlContext.sql('SELECT OP.`Provider State` AS State, OP.`Provider City` AS City, OP.`Provider Id` AS Provider_ID,\
                ROUND(OP.average_OP_cost) AS Average_OP_Cost, ROUND(IP.average_IP_cost) AS Average_IP_Cost, ROUND(OP.average_OP_cost + IP.average_IP_cost) AS Combined_Average_Cost\
                FROM ( SELECT `Provider State`,`Provider City`,`Provider Id`,SUM(`Average Total Payments`*`Outpatient Services`)/SUM(`Outpatient Services`) AS average_OP_cost\
                FROM outPatientAll GROUP BY `Provider State`, `Provider City`, `Provider Id` ) AS OP\
                INNER JOIN ( SELECT `Provider State`, `Provider City`,`Provider Id`,SUM(`Average Medicare Payments`*`Total Discharges`)/SUM(`Total Discharges`) AS average_IP_cost\
                FROM inPatientAll GROUP BY `Provider State`,`Provider City`, `Provider Id` ) AS IP\
                ON OP.`Provider Id` = IP.`Provider Id` AND OP.`Provider State` = IP.`Provider State` AND OP.`Provider City` = IP.`Provider City`\
                ORDER BY combined_average_cost DESC')

%pyspark
test2 = sqlContext.sql('SELECT OP.`Provider State` AS State, OP.`Provider City` AS City, OP.`Provider Id` AS Provider_ID,\
                ROUND(OP.average_OP_cost) AS Average_OP_Cost, ROUND(IP.average_IP_cost) AS Average_IP_Cost, ROUND(OP.average_OP_cost + IP.average_IP_cost) AS Combined_Average_Cost\
                FROM ( SELECT `Provider State`,`Provider City`,`Provider Id`,SUM(`Average Total Payments`*`Outpatient Services`)/SUM(`Outpatient Services`) AS average_OP_cost\
                FROM outPatientAll GROUP BY `Provider State`, `Provider City`, `Provider Id` ) AS OP\
                INNER JOIN ( SELECT `Provider State`, `Provider City`,`Provider Id`,SUM(`Average Medicare Payments`*`Total Discharges`)/SUM(`Total Discharges`) AS average_IP_cost\
                FROM inPatientAll GROUP BY `Provider State`,`Provider City`, `Provider Id` ) AS IP\
                ON OP.`Provider Id` = IP.`Provider Id` AND OP.`Provider State` = IP.`Provider State` AND OP.`Provider City` = IP.`Provider City`\
                ORDER BY combined_average_cost')

%pyspark
top10 = test.limit(10)
bottom10 = test2.limit(10)

%pyspark
z.show(top10)

%pyspark
z.show(bottom10)
